
[1]sensibly

   SENS'IBLY, adv.

   1. In a manner to be perceived by the senses; perceptibly to the
   senses; as pain sensibly increased; motion sensibly accelerated.

   2. With perception, either of mind or body. He feels his loss very
   sensibly.

   3. Externally; by affecting the senses.

   4. With quick intellectual perception.

   5. With intelligence or good sense; judiciously. The man converses very
   sensibly on all common topics.
